##

EXAMPLE: tests/grouped_return_expression.stult

This example checks that grouped return expressions are not mistaken for loops.

A function return expression may start with a grouped expression:

	((A + B) * C)

That expression starts with touching "((", but it is not a loop statement
because it appears where an expression is required.

##

PRINT : STD["IO"]["PRINT"]
STRING_NEW : STD["TYPE"]["STRING"]["NEW"]

SCALE_SUM : { (A, B, C)
	((A + B) * C)
}

RESULT : SCALE_SUM(2, 3, 4)

PRINT("result: " + STRING_NEW(RESULT))